      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARCHER THIRTEEN (2) proved too good on debut over 366m at Capalaba to score by 5 lengths (19.85). Drawn to take advantage of good early pace. Rates on top again. TO XIBALBA (1) turned in a strong run last time, placing in a Grade 6 when second behind Lakoda Bonnie in a swift 29.83 and setting a new course and distance PB. Looks a leading chance again. HARA'S TYRION (3) has been hard to follow lately, running sixth (31.25) last time but prior to that ran very well when placed at this track. Expected to do much better this time. CRYSTAL DAYS (7) is a Raymond Burman-trained newcomer by Equalizer out of Champagne Jazzy. Start all important and will need some luck getting across from the wide draw. Market should provide a lead to her ability.",
